description.0: Man-Thing's ‘chemical treatment' leaves him entirely transformed. The Mad Viking perishes.
description.2: As you read this issue, ask yourself: how would you escape being Dracula's next meal?
description.3: The return of Gwen Stacy! Upon his return from France, Peter learns that Gwen is not only alive and well, but waiting for him in his apartment! Mac Gargan, A.K.A. Scorpion, gains access to his Scorpion armor and returns to a life of crime. Will Spider-Man be able to solve the mystery of Gwen's return, and take down Scorpion?
description.4: The X-Men's Beast makes a surprise cameo; however his arrival is fraught with bad news. The X-Men have gone into hiding following anti-mutant hysteria, and Hank McCoy seeks the aid of Avenger, Iron Man. Desperate, madly in love, and depressed by humanity's rejection, Beast finds himself in dire circumstances with the Brant Corporation.
description.5: Revealed at last! The true facts behind the origin of the Falcon! Will this be the end of the Dynamic Duo?
description.7: The Puppet Master and Radion team up and force Thor to destroy the Fantastic Four.
description.8: Are the Defenders prepared to take on the Sons of the Serpent?
description.11: Peter and Joe Robertson continue their bid to bring J. Jonah Jameson home after he is kidnapped in Paris. Stateside, Aunt May sees a young woman that is the spitting image of the deceased Gwen Stacy! Is this a strange apparition? Or has Gwen Stacy returned from the dead?
description.12: The Vision discovers that Ultron played a significant role in his transformation from human to sentient A.I. Moondragon tells Mantis that she is the runner-up "Celestial Madonna", should Mantis prove unworthy of the title.
description.13: With Captain America hopelessly outnumbered, will the Red Skull finally triumph? Prepare for an unbelievable ending!
description.16: Citrusville becomes ever more vigilant in its watch against Man-Thing. The Mad Viking turns his wrath towards Florida's education system.
description.19: It is revealed that Glenn Talbot is being held captive at a Soviet base in Siberia! Can General Ross, S.H.I.E.L.D.'s Nick Fury and Clay Quartermain save Talbot...without Bruce Banner's help?
description.20: The war of the super-villains has begun and its first causality is Iron Man! The battle you demanded-Modok versus the Thinker-and the Golden Avenger is caught in the middle of it all!
description.21: The Absorbing Man is looking to take the fight to Thor and when he absorbs the power of Mjolnir, he might have enough might to do so. Plus, Hercules and Sif prepare for the threat that is Kamo Tharn.
description.22: Quincy Harker believes he has the necessary deathtraps and accoutrement to kill Dracula. The Lord of Vampires is led through a fatal maze in Harker's estate!
description.23: With the Inhuman royal palace under siege by Xemu of the 5th Dimension, Quicksilver is sent to retrieve Medusa by order of Black Bolt. The rest of the FF head to the Hidden Land to take the palace back. But are they headed straight into a trap?
description.26: PANTHER'S RAGE PART 10: The Panther is greeted by Salamander K'Ruel, one of Killmonger's agents, in the Forest of Thorns.
description.28: The Orbiting Space Station is nearly taken by Hate-Monger and Red Hate! Meanwhile, J. Jonah Jameson takes heat from the FBI as they probe into the disappearance of his son.
description.35: The Defenders battle bigotry in New York City!
description.38: The Squadron Sinister returns and leads to a severe injury that will have big consequences for the life of Nighthawk.
description.39: Warlock is captured by a species unfamiliar, in a ship unknown. He'll stick around for a little just to learn more about this strange race, but his break out is imminent!
description.47: Attack of the Mad Viking! An overly macho man launches an attack against those who don't fit his definition of ‘masculine'. Man-Thing interrupts Viking's berserker rage in the nick of time.
description.50: Spider-Man continues to hallucinate thanks to Mysterio's mind-warping abilities. After Jameson is kidnapped, Joe Robertson and Peter travel to France with nearly a million dollars for his ransom. Plus, Peter and MJ share their first kiss!
description.51: With half of the Avengers in Kree space, the team receives a lesson in military history of the Kree-Cotati wars. In Limbo, the Vision re-lives his past as the original Human Torch. Meanwhile, Moondragon shows up to the abandoned Avengers Mansion, following the summons of Captain Marvel.
description.52: The Red Skull is back to exact revenge on Captain America once again! But will there be an innocent lost in their never ending war of good versus evil?
description.54: Johnny Blaze enters the Desolation Run, a motorcycle race across the vast wilds of America. But when the Inferno-possessed Hulk crashes the scene, Blaze has no choice but to unleash hellfire!
description.55: Hulk is incapacitated in a deprivation tank! Meanwhile, Hulkbuster scientist Captain Kirkman turns out to not only be a Russian spy...but The Devastator!
description.56: Loki and his army are winning the war and Thor and the US army might have to consider a final, desperate action.
description.57: Dracula begins his takedown of the British Parliament...by killing a parliamentarian's daughter! Taj Nitall faces a tough choice - kill his own son or sacrifice his village.
description.58: The mighty Morbius has battled Spider-Man and many other powerful heroes, but he finally may have met his maker!
description.59: The Silver Surfer is trying to revive the memory of Shalla-Bal, while the FF battles Doomsman II- who wields the Power Cosmic! Will Doctor Doom's plan to eliminate the Fantastic Four follow through? Or is there a larger plan in motion?
description.61: Kowalski enters the body of Colonel Sessue Takeda to grapple with the fate of his ex-wife or son. One, or both, must fall.
description.62: Simon Stroud effectively hunted Man-Wolf… and now he’s added a certain vampire to his list!
description.63: The most cosmic super hero of them all takes off beyond the skies! Featuring Ant-Man & the Wasp!
description.64: On Christmas Eve, Mr. Fantastic discovers a new star above Arizona and the Thing investigates. Miracle Man reenacts Biblical Bethlehem to become a god!
description.65: The Headmen turn the citizens of New York into enraged rioters. Can the Defenders stop Manhattan from descending into madness?
description.69: Spider-Man questions his sanity after fighting a reincarnated Mysterio. Mysterio continues to terrorize Spider-Man with mind games, some of which carry over into his civilian life. Plus, J. Jonah Jameson's connection to Mysterio revealed!
description.70: The astral form of the Swordsman is revealed to be Zodiac member Libra! In the depths of Limbo, Immortus gives Vision and Mantis the opportunity to step into their pasts and discover their origins. The Scarlet Witch continues to hone her magical abilities under the tutelage of Agatha Harkness.
description.71: The death of a hero! Can Steve Rogers move on from his old life? Or will the death of a comrade suck him back into the world of Captain America!
description.72: John finds security with Joel and Mary, but it doesn't last long when Man-Wolf's apprehended by a gang of crooks! J. Jonah Jameson shows up, and he has a few pointers for his son, (don't kill anyone).
description.75: A chapter from Ted Sallis' past leads to a horrifying nightmare in the present. Sainte-Cloud, a former friend of Sallis', buys a Man-Thing candle, but is unaware of its hallucinogenic properties.
description.80: PANTHER'S RAGE PART 9: The Panther follows Killmonger to Serpent Valley, where a prehistoric beast attacks him!
description.84: A visit from President Gerald Ford turns ugly when Armbruster's suspicions about Glenn Talbot are confirmed! Betty is conflicted when a battle breaks out between her father and the Hulk.
description.85: When Iron Man's friends are held captive, the Golden Avenger rockets into action! Facing the combined forces of the Crimson Dynamo and Kuan Set, Iron Man must use wit and strength to save the day!
description.86: Loki's armies attack Earth and Thor has to marshall the US Army to defend our world. Plus, where has Odin gone?
description.87: Wracked by grief over Shiela's suicide, Dracula recalls past occurrences where he was similarly bereft. Blade the Vampire Hunter guest-stars!
description.88: The Fantastic Four are handed over to Doctor Doom on a Silver (Surfer) platter! But the Doctor has bigger plans for the FF and Surfer before eliminating them. After all, Doom does have a point to prove!
description.93: The Avengers - trapped in Limbo! Iron Man - dead! The Vision - mortally wounded! KANG WAR II hurtles towards its shocking conclusion!
description.95: The ever-lovin' Thing joins forces with the Defenders to save a Valkyrie ambushed by the Undying Ones!

0.text: Man-Thing's ‘chemical treatment' leaves him entirely transformed. The Mad Viking perishes.

1.text: An unlikely sacrifice frees Lissa from her lycanthropic curse!

6.text: Deathlok continues to battle Ryker’s men, but meets a true foe in a massive tank powered by Nina’s mind. Meanwhile, Mike Travers escapes his cell and continues his hunt for Deathlok.

7.text: The Puppet Master and Radion team up and force Thor to destroy the Fantastic Four.

8.text: Are the Defenders prepared to take on the Sons of the Serpent?

14.text: Criminal organization I.C.O.N. is dead set on perfecting their super soldier program. Unfortunately, Frankenstein’s Monster may pay the price! I.C.O.N. kidnaps the Monster, all in the name of ethically-unsound science. Will the monster’s genetics hold the key to I.C.O.N.'s success?

15.text: Man-Thing saves a girl who is attacked with fire for trying to expose a corrupt school system.

16.text: Citrusville becomes ever more vigilant in its watch against Man-Thing. The Mad Viking turns his wrath towards Florida's education system.

17.text: As the battle ensues between the beast-versions of the Russell siblings, Buck and Topaz try to keep the two from killing each other!

18.text: Nelson and Murdock are Attorneys at Law, but now Foggy Nelson is…an agent of S.H.I.E.L.D?!

25.text: Sir Denis Nayland Smith has been kidnapped, and an esoteric message on a bamboo scroll is the only lead Shang-Chi has!

26.text: PANTHER’S RAGE PART 10: The Panther is greeted by Salamander K'Ruel, one of Killmonger’s agents, in the Forest of Thorns.

30.text: Nighthawk requests the aid of Spider-Man to track down the Looter, a brazen thief who has stolen a natural artifact from Nighthawk’s talons!

31.text: Killraven, M'Shulla and Mint Julep may fall prey to the Martian Masters’ High Overlord!

34.text: Strange heads to the Dark Dimension to take on Umar and her demonic army!

35.text: The Defenders battle bigotry in New York City!

36.text: The Human Torch needs help, and only the Son of Satan can give it! Wyatt Wingfoot has been possessed by a shadowy force, so Johnny Storm seeks out the best exorcist in the world - Daimon Hellstrom!

37.text: Daimon is ambushed by the malevolent Madam Swabada, and to make matters worse, the police are after him as well!

40.text: Martial Arts Mayhem or Moral Violence? The Master of Kung Fu is back in “A Different Lesson in Blood Unchanged!”

41.text: Power Man visits the circus! Let’s hope he doesn’t become the main act!

42.text: The Werewolf finds himself yet again locked in a deadly battle - this time, against MORBIUS, the Living Vampire! Plus, classic tales of Marvel horror throughout the ages!

43.text: Shang-Chi confronts his father over a cold-blooded murder at long last!

47.text: Attack of the Mad Viking! An overly macho man launches an attack against those who don't fit his definition of ‘masculine'. Man-Thing interrupts Viking's berserker rage in the nick of time.

48.text: Approaching Lissa’s 18th birthday, the gang fears she will succumb to the Russoff curse…!

53.text: Matt Murdock quickly has to spring into action as Daredevil when a group of terrorists take to an airport fully strapped!

63.text: The most cosmic super hero of them all takes off beyond the skies! Featuring Ant-Man & the Wasp!

64.text: On Christmas Eve, Mr. Fantastic discovers a new star above Arizona and the Thing investigates. Miracle Man reenacts Biblical Bethlehem to become a god!

65.text: The Headmen turn the citizens of New York into enraged rioters. Can the Defenders stop Manhattan from descending into madness?

66.text: Danny receives a mystical vision at the Temple of Kali. Who are the Living Goddesses, and what do they want with Colleen Wing? Colleen and her father are in grave danger, but an ancient text may hold the key to their freedom. The Ninja reveals his true identity!

67.text: Count Dracula encounters a creature more terrifying than himself!

68.text: Killraven and the Freemen obliterate Death-Birth, a Martian stronghold!

73.text: Kem Horkus has asked Ka-Zar's help in seeking revenge against the one who betrayed his family!

74.text: The Monster gets a violent education in the modern world when the Jigsaw Nightmare comes out to play! These clone-creatures have Frankenstein’s creation reeling- has the Monster met his match?

75.text: A chapter from Ted Sallis' past leads to a horrifying nightmare in the present. Sainte-Cloud, a former friend of Sallis', buys a Man-Thing candle, but is unaware of its hallucinogenic properties.

76.text: A menace dwells within the beach caves of Los Angeles, and he possesses Topaz’s soul in an egg-shaped stone!

77.text: Enter another Kung Fu master! Iron Fist stars in “Slay Now, Die Later”! Who is Danny Rand?

78.text: Followed by the British Secret Service? Nearly suffocated in a car? Confronted by an enemy he thought he'd already killed? Just a day in the life of Shang-Chi!

79.text: Sir Denis is after the long-lost Golden Beetle relic of the pharaoh Seth-Amon -- a legend relayed to him in a dream by none other than Fah Lo Suee…Shang-Chi's sister.

80.text: PANTHER’S RAGE PART 9: The Panther follows Killmonger to Serpent Valley, where a prehistoric beast attacks him!

82.text: Doctor Doom crash-lands in the ocean and is discovered by none other than the King of Atlantis! Will Namor play nice with a still-incapacitated Doom? The answer will surprise you! The beginning of a new alliance between two of Marvel’s heaviest hitters!

83.text: Responding to a call from the owner of Fogwell's Gym, Daredevil learns the story of a young man who hopes to become a heavyweight fighter.

91.text: Iron Fist gains the attention of Spider-Man! In one of their strangest battles yet, the two street-level heroes go toe-to-toe against Drom, a villain who is aging in reverse.

93.text: The Avengers - trapped in Limbo! Iron Man - dead! The Vision - mortally wounded! KANG WAR II hurtles towards its shocking conclusion!

94.text: Umar the Unrelenting has returned to the earthly plane and is up to her usual sorcery. Will Strange uncover her true purpose in New York?

95.text: The ever-lovin' Thing joins forces with the Defenders to save a Valkyrie ambushed by the Undying Ones!

99.text: The Ringmaster returns! The leader of The Circus of Crime has been secretly filming Daredevil…but to what end?
